<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7121.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">Winslow</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>U. S. S. “<hi rend="smallcaps">San Diego</hi>,” <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Topolobampo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>M–3245. Troop train under General Estrada left Guaymas for Yaqui Valley
                            this morning. General Manso with troop train passed through Hermosillo
                            this morning and is expected in Empalme about noon. General Obregon
                            ordered sixty cars to Hermosillo to carry more troops south; twenty-five
                            of these have already been sent from Empalme. Consul has telegraphed to
                            Esperanza for report of conditions and troop movements.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winslow.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
